Description: Rhesus macaques immunized with 5x1010 viral particles Ad26.COV2.S (N=5).

Description: Rhesus macaques immunized with 1.125x1010 viral particles Ad26.COV2.S (N=5).

Name: Participants in a longitudinal observational study
Description: Participants in the longitudinal observational PARIS (Protection Associated with Rapid Immunity to SARS-CoV-2) study (n=30).

Name: Moderna Vaccine recipients
Description: Subjects received mRNA-1273 and donated blood at different times post-vaccination (n=30).

Name: Pfizer/BioNTech Vaccine recipients
Description: Subjects received BNT162b2 and donated blood at different times post-vaccination (n=30).

Name: Janssen Vaccine recipients
Description: Subjects received Ad26.COV2.S and donated blood at different times post-vaccination (n=30).

Name: Novavax Vaccine recipients
Description: Subjects received NVX-CoV2373 and donated blood at different times post-vaccination (n=12).

Name: HCW prior SARS-CoV-2
Description: Health Care workers with prior infection confirmed by PCR, antigen test, and/or detectable antibody levels to spike, RBD, and Nucleocapsid

Name: HCW SARS-CoV-2 naïve
Description: Health Care Workers with no prior infection

Name: NH residents prior SARS-CoV-2
Description: Nursing home residents with prior infection confirmed by PCR, antigen test, and/or detectable antibody levels to spike, RBD, and Nucleocapsid

Name: NH residents SARS-CoV-2 naïve
Description: Nursing home residents with no prior infection.

Name: COVID-19 convalescent plasma (CCP) donors
Description: COVID-19 convalescent plasma (CCP) donors from the San Francisco Bay Area in California (n=93)

Name: COVID-19 patients
Description: COVID-19 patients admitted to Stanford Hospital (n=16)

Name: Vaccinated mongolian participants
Description: Mongolian participants who had been fully vaccinated with one of four COVID vaccines: Pfizer/BioNTech (BNT162b2), AstraZeneca (ChAdOx1-S), Sputnik V (Gam-COVID-Vac), and Sinopharm (BBIBP-CorV). (n=196)

Name: Individuals with breakthrough infections
Description: Participants who had a history of SARS-CoV-2 infection after vaccination (n=99)

Name: Volunteer blood donor
Description: A volunteer's blood donor, healthy on the day of donation, who had detectable SARS-CoV-2 RNA levels in their blood at least 40 days after resolution of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19)–like symptoms (n=1).

Name: COVID-19 Patient Samples
Description: Patients admitted to Stanford Hospital with signs and symptoms of COVID-19 and confirmed SARS-CoV-2 infection (n=13)

Name: Healthy Human Control Samples
Description: Healthy adults with no signs or symptoms of acute illness or disease (n=114)

Name: One time COVID-19 infected samples
Description: Individuals previously infected with  a Washington-1-like SARS-CoV-2 strain (n = 24)

Name: 2 doses of Moderna mRNA-1273
Description: Subjects received two doses of Moderna mRNA-1273 vaccination (n = 14)

Name: 2 doses of Pfizer BNT162b2
Description: Subjects received two doses of Pfizer BNT162b2 vaccination (n = 14)

Name: Two doses of NVX-CoV2373
Description: Subjects received two doses of NVX-CoV2373 vaccination (n = 10)

Name: One dose of Ad26.COV2.S
Description: Subjects received one dose of Ad26.COV2.S vaccination (n = 10)

Name: Two doses of AZD1222
Description: Subjects received two doses of AZD1222 (n = 16)

Name: Two doses of Sputnik V
Description: Subjects received two doses of Sputnik V vaccination (n = 12)

Name: Two doses of Sinopharm BBIBPCorV
Description: Subjects received two doses of Sinopharm BBIBPCorV vaccination (n = 12)

Name: Three doses of Moderna mRNA-1273 or Pfizer BNT162b2
Description: Subjects received three doses of Moderna mRNA-1273 or Pfizer BNT162b2 (n = 13)

Name: Two doses NVX-CoV2373 + one dose of BNT162b2 or NVX-CoV2373
Description: Subjects received Two doses NVX-CoV2373 + one dose of BNT162b2 or NVX-CoV2373 (n = 5)

Name: One dose of Ad26.COV2.S + one dose of Ad26.COV2.S or BNT162b2
Description: Subjects received one dose of Ad26.COV2.S + one dose of Ad26.COV2.S or BNT162b2 (N=14)

Name: Two doses of AZD1222  + one dose of BNT162b2 or mRNA-1273
Description: Subjects received two doses of AZD1222  + one dose of BNT162b2 or mRNA-1273 (n = 18)

Description: Subjects received two doses of Sputnik V + one dose of AZD1222 or BNT162b2 (N=14)

Description: Subjects received two doses of Sinopharm BBIBP-CorV +one dose of BNT162b2 or mRNA-1273 (N=18)

Name: Seronegative health care workers (NHCW).
Description: Seronegative health care workers from Miami cohort (n = 32), whose samples were collected in between Apr-Jun 2020.

Name: PCR positive health care workers (PHCW).
Description: PCR positive health care workers from Maimi cohort (n = 26), whose samples were collected in Aug 2020.

Name: Community volunteers (SIP).
Description: Community volunteers who were all seronegative and with no exposure to known infected persons from Miami cohort (n = 33), whose samples were collected in Jun 2020.

Name: Unexposed donors from San Diego (NSD).
Description: Asymptomatic unexposed and seronegative donors from San Diego cohort (NSD) (n = 15), whose samples were collected in between Mar-Jun 2020.

Name: COVID-19 seropositive subjects also from the San Diego region (COVID-19 SD).
Description: COVID-19 seropositive subjects from the San Diego cohort (COVID-19 SD) (n = 10), whose samples were collected in between Apr-Jul 2020.

Name: Non-CCP recipients
Description: COVID-19 infected patients who did not received COVID-19 convalescent plasma (CCP) (N= 363)

Name: CCP EAP Recipients
Description: COVID-19 infected patients who received COVID-19 convalescent plasma (CCP) as treatment (N= 163)

Name: Pregnant cohort
Description: Pregnant women who tested either positive (n = 22) or negative (n = 11) for SARS-CoV-2 before delivery at the Johns Hopkins Hospital.

Name: Nonpregnant cohort
Description: Nonpregnant women who tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 at the Johns Hopkins Hospital (n = 17).

Name: Solid organ transplant recipients (SOTRs)
Description: Solid organ transplant recipients (SOTRs) initially received two doses of an mRNA-based vaccine and 70% of participants received a third mRNA vaccine dose and 30% received the Janssen Ad26.COV2.S vaccine (n = 47).

Name: Heathy controls
Description: Heathy controls all received two doses of BNT162b2 vaccination (n = 15).

Name: Healthy vaccinated individuals
Description: Healthy individuals with the BNT162b2 vaccination (n = 53).

Name: Individuals with natural infection
Description: Individuals with natural infection (n = 106).

Name: Healthy vaccinated individuals
Description: Healthy individuals with the mRNA-1273 vaccine (n = 49)

Name: Bone marrow-derived mast cells (BMMC)
Description: Mouse bone marrow-derived mast cell (BMMC) cultures from huFcεRIα transgenic mice.

Name: Human basophils
Description: Human basophils were collected from volunteers with grass allergies (n = 4).

Name: Postvaccine myocarditis cohort
Description: Adolescents and young adults with vaccine-associated myocarditis (n = 16).

Name: Controls
Description: Age-matched asymptomatic vaccinated control subjects (n = 45).

Name: Children with MIS-C with myocarditis
Description: Children with multisystem inflammatory syndrome in children (MIS-C) with myocarditis were previously enrolled in the MGH Pediatric COVID-19 Biorepository (n = 10)

Name: BNT162b2 vaccine group
Description: Participants received BNT162b2 vaccination (n = 27).

Name: Ad26.COV2.S vaccine group
Description: Participants received Ad26.COV2.S vaccination (n = 20).

Name: Patients that tested positive for COVID-19
Description: Patients who presented to the Emergency Department that tested positive for COVID-19 (n=306).

User Defined ID: Patients that tested negative for COVID-19
Name: Healthy Controls
Description: Patients who presented to the Emergency Department that tested negative for COVID-19 (n=78) and were used as controls.

Name: Healthy Controls
Description: Healthy donors from which blood was collected (n=8).

Name: Lung cancer patients
Description: Lung cancer patients from New York City.

Name: Peripheral B cells
Description: Peripheral B cells from healthy donors were used to create non-immunized scFv-phage libraries.

Name: Syrian golden hamsters
Description: Syrian golden hamsters challenged with SARS-CoV-2 by the intranasal (IN) route on day 0. On day 1 post-challenge hamsters were treated with 5 mg/kg of monoclonal antibodies via intraperitoneal route (IP).

Name: Control group of hamsters
Description: Syrian golden hamsters challenged with SARS-CoV-2 by the intranasal (IN) route on day 0. On day 1 post-challenge hamsters received sterile PBS via the intraperitoneal route.

Name: BALB/c mice
Description: Mice were injected intraperitoneally with the appropriate concentration of each mAb combination 12 hours prior to infection. Mice were infected intranasally with SARS-CoV-2 MA or SARS-CoV-2 WT.

Name: Vero E6 cells
Description: Vero E6 cells were infected with the SARS-CoV-2 variants.

Name: HEK293F- hACE2 cells
Description: hACE2- expressing HEK293F cells infected with HIV- 1 pseudotyped with D614G spike.
